    "It would also prohibit the unauthorized modification of outsourced EHRs [28].In their study Sun et al.",
    "also proposed a blockchainbased solution for medical record data storage and sharing (MedRSS) by combining a hyperledger fabric blockchain with the InterPlanetary File System.",
    "Their MedRSS solution contained central entities whose names were the Control module and the Regulator, which was vulnerable to attacks [29].In another study Mohammed et al.",
    "designed a decentralized authentication system using blockchain and bioacoustics signals for secure access to medical records.",
    "Although the authors stated that their study was cloudbased, it is seen that medical records are were stored on the blockchain [30].Quan et al."
